5737 5739 5742
Survey of the Mirror Flats crossing routes is needed to update the Reach cartographic record. Salt cricket swarm leaders occupy the cricket breeding grounds north of the Swift Line, cairn kite alphas have claimed elevated survey points along Crystal Ridge, and corrupted Warden toll-thieves are interfering with caravan data collection at approach checkpoints. Engage one of each and return field observations to the cartography office.
The Mirror Flats survey data has been incorporated into the updated Reach cartographic record. Cricket swarm pressure along the northern Swift Line and kite territory at Crystal Ridge are now properly documented, and the interference from corrupted toll-thieves at the approach checkpoints has been cleared. The cartography office has issued updated crossing advisories to all registered caravan operators.

